From: Eric Dumazet <eric.dumazet@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 20 Oct 2011 09:22:18 +0000
Subject: igbvf: fix truesize underestimation
Patch-mainline: v3.2-rc1
Git-commit: 7b8b59617ead5acc6ff041a9ad2ea1fe7a58094f
References: bnc#795299 FATE#313657

igbvf allocates half a page per skb fragment. We must account
PAGE_SIZE/2 increments on skb->truesize, not the actual frag length.

Signed-off-by: Eric Dumazet <eric.dumazet@gmail.com>
CC: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/netdev.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/netdev.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igbvf/netdev.c
@@ -312,7 +312,7 @@ static bool igbvf_clean_rx_irq(struct ig
 
 			skb->len += length;
 			skb->data_len += length;
-			skb->truesize += length;
+			skb->truesize += PAGE_SIZE / 2;
 		}
 send_up:
 		i++;
